  "title": "calling toString on random objects can cause errors in IE",
  "body": "<!--\r\n  Thanks for participating in this project! We will try to answer as soon as possible 🙏\r\n-->\r\n\r\n**Describe the bug 🐛**\r\nA clear and concise description of what the bug is.\r\n\r\n**To Reproduce 🔍**\r\nSteps to reproduce the behavior:\r\n1. Go to IE11\r\n2. see an error\r\n\r\n\r\nA live example helps a lot!   We have a simple online template for you to use for your explanations:\r\n\r\nfor now: https://nopproj.computeruniverse.net/de/search?cid=0&query=\r\n\r\n**Expected behavior 💭**\r\n\r\nNo errors\r\n\r\n\r\n**Screenshots 🖥**\r\n\r\n<img width=\"805\" alt=\"Screenshot 2019-05-27 at 15 49 22\" src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/6270048/58426338-75231e00-809c-11e9-9b73-c10c450f6408.png\">\r\n\r\n\r\n**Environment:**\r\n - OS: Windows\r\n - Browser: IE\r\n - Version: 11\r\n\r\n**Additional context**\r\n\r\n\r\ntoString.call can not be called on a string in IE, we should check for that first https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch.js/blob/9dca5480d27265a92f9e0f0cc7405b1c33badd0e/src/lib/utils/isPlainObject.ts#L11",
